65
00:07:37,610 --> 00:07:38,940
One minute ten.

66
00:07:39,480 --> 00:07:41,070
Why are you telling me this?

67
00:07:41,400 --> 00:07:43,860
Because there are things we need to know.

68
00:07:44,410 --> 00:07:48,030
Otherwise, the same thing that
you let happen to your people up there...

69
00:07:48,080 --> 00:07:51,870
...could happen to ours,
and we would accomplish nothing.

70
00:07:52,330 --> 00:07:54,500
-I have about one minute left?
-About.

71
00:07:54,750 --> 00:07:57,460
The small monolith
you brought back from the moon....

72
00:07:57,500 --> 00:08:02,220
Your government has been very selfish
and stupid in keeping it to yourselves.

73
00:08:02,420 --> 00:08:05,680
You never let us examine it.
What have you found out about it?

74
00:08:05,720 --> 00:08:06,800
Nothing.

75
00:08:07,010 --> 00:08:08,300
It's impenetrable.

76
00:08:08,930 --> 00:08:12,140
We've tried lasers, nuclear detonators.
Nothing worked.

77
00:08:12,680 --> 00:08:13,810
Forty-five seconds.

78
00:08:13,850 --> 00:08:16,520
The monolith near Jupiter, 
it is the same?

79
00:08:16,770 --> 00:08:18,150
It's even larger.

80
00:08:18,770 --> 00:08:22,150
And the computer on board the Discovery...

81
00:08:22,280 --> 00:08:25,110
...the HAL-9000, can it be reactivated?

82
00:08:25,360 --> 00:08:26,410
Yes.

83
00:08:26,610 --> 00:08:28,280
-By us?
-By you?

84
