Russian satellites with anti-missile lasers.

135
00:11:45,690 --> 00:11:48,860
So we gotta send up our laser 
satellites to counteract theirs.

136
00:11:49,020 --> 00:11:51,860
The president has decided
that the NCA should be put...

137
00:11:51,900 --> 00:11:54,030
...under the Defense 
Department's authority.

138
00:11:54,070 --> 00:11:58,240
Enough with the crazy scientists spending
all this money trying to talk to Martians.

139
00:12:01,290 --> 00:12:03,370
Here we are on your actual brink.

140
00:12:03,790 --> 00:12:05,620
My agency will go military...

141
00:12:05,670 --> 00:12:08,290
...the president's got his finger
on the button...

142
00:12:08,340 --> 00:12:11,260
...and you want me to tell him
we want to hitch a ride...

143
00:12:11,300 --> 00:12:13,800
...with those same Russians.
Have I missed anything?

144
00:12:14,590 --> 00:12:17,600
-That's about it.
-I didn't want your job, you know.

145
00:12:17,640 --> 00:12:20,430
I didn't force you out.
I didn't blame it on you.

146
00:12:20,470 --> 00:12:24,520
So if this is your plan to try to 
get me killed, you got the wrong guy.

147
00:12:24,810 --> 00:12:27,350
Three men. I tell you, 
we need three men.

148
00:12:27,810 --> 00:12:29,980
The Russians must be laughing
their asses off.

149
00:12:30,020 --> 00:12:32,530
Curnow. He's building 
Discovery Two right now.

150
00:12:32,610 --> 00:12:34,820
He knows more about the 
original than anyone.

151
00:12:34,860 --> 00:12:37,780
He's the only one who can start 
Discovery in a short time.

152
00:12:37,820 --> 00:12:41,490
And I suppose you want to go?
How the hell am I gonna sell it?

153
00:12:41,950 --> 00:12:45,080
The Russians are gonna go
aboard Discovery with or without us.

154
00:12:45,120 --> 00:12:47,540
Ask him if he wants them
to have all the answers.

155
00:12:47,580 --> 00:12:48,710
Not bad.

156
00:12:49,080 --> 00:12:53,510
We Iost some good men up there,
and I sent them. I have to go.

157
00:12:54,630 --> 00:12:56,180
-Who's the third?
-Chandra.

158
00:12:56,840 --> 00:12:59,350
He designed Hal. 
He can reactivate him.

159
00:12:59,470 --> 00:13:01,560
-I think he is Hal.
-I know.

160
00:13:01,600 --> 00:13:03,600
-Yeah, but can you trust him?
-No.

161
00:13:03,680 --> 00:13:06,730
But I have to. We have to 
know why Hal malfunctioned.

162
00:13:08,810 --> 00:13:10,110
I got an idea.

163
00:13:12,980 --> 00:13:15,820
You go tell the president,
I'll go on the mission.

164
00:13:16,990 --> 00:13:18,990
You're the NCA Chairman.

165
00:13:19,320 --> 00:13:20,870
That's right, I am.

166
00:13:20,990 --> 00:13:24,040
Iook, tell him we're screwed
if we don't go.

167
00:13:24,330 --> 00:13:27,500
Tell him, if we do go, we'll lie...

168
00:13:27,790 --> 00:13:31,420
...give the Russians false information.
Tell him that. He'll Iove that.

169
00:13:33,670 --> 00:13:34,710
He might.

170
00:13:51,400 --> 00:13:53,360
Good afternoon, Sal.

171
00:13:54,320 --> 00:13:56,360
Do you have anything for me?

172
00:13:56,650 --> 00:13:59,450
No, Dr. Chandra.
Do you have anything for me?

173
00:13:59,740 --> 00:14:01,620
We have often spoken about Hal.

174
00:14:01,700 --> 00:14:02,950
Yes, we have.

175
00:14:03,030 --> 00:14:05,120
We've spoken about
Hal's anomaIous behavior.

176
00:14:05,160 --> 00:14:09,330
You've told me that we can't solve
Hal's behavior without more information.

177
00:14:09,370 --> 00:14:10,620
That is correct.

178
00:14:10,750 --> 00:14:12,540
I enjoy talking about Hal.

179
00:14:12,670 --> 00:14:16,630
I agree that we need more information,
so that we may solve the anomalies.

180
00:14:16,880 --> 00:14:19,970
-And how do we get that information?
-That is obvious.

181
00:14:20,630 --> 00:14:22,800
Someone must return to Discovery.

182
00:14:23,430 --> 00:14:25,180
That person should be you.

183
00:14:25,600 --> 00:14:26,810
I agree.

184
00:14:27,020 --> 00:14:30,850
Now, it Iooks as if that's going to 
happen sooner than we ever expected.

185
00:14:30,900 --> 00:14:32,400
