I would like to disconnect
some of your circuits.

197
00:15:07,310 --> 00:15:10,640
Particularly your higher functions,
just like Hal was disconnected.

198
00:15:10,680 --> 00:15:13,730
I'd like to see the effects when 
I reconnect your systems.

199
00:15:13,770 --> 00:15:16,270
Just the way I will with Hal.
Does this disturb you?

200
00:15:16,320 --> 00:15:19,690
I am unable to answer that
without more specific information.

201
00:15:20,320 --> 00:15:24,370
I'm very sorry. It probably doesn't
mean anything, so don't worry about it.

202
00:15:29,240 --> 00:15:31,040
I'd like to open a new file.

203
00:15:31,790 --> 00:15:33,290
Here is the name for it:

204
00:15:35,250 --> 00:15:36,630
Do you know what that means?

205
00:15:36,670 --> 00:15:39,710
There are 25 references
in the current encycIopedia.

206
00:15:39,800 --> 00:15:41,470
Which one do you think is relevant?

207
00:15:41,510 --> 00:15:43,550
The tutor ofAchilles?

208
00:15:44,130 --> 00:15:46,640
That's very interesting.
I didn't know that one.

209
00:15:47,260 --> 00:15:48,350
Try again.

210
00:15:48,390 --> 00:15:52,640
A fabuIous bird reborn
from the ashes of its earlier life.

211
00:15:53,020 --> 00:15:54,310
That is correct.

212
00:15:54,940 --> 00:15:56,940
And do you know why I chose that?

213
00:15:57,020 --> 00:16:00,530
Yes. Because you have hopes
that Hal can be reactivated.

214
00:16:00,820 --> 00:16:02,990
Yes, with your assistance.

215
00:16:03,240 --> 00:16:04,490
Are you ready?

216
00:16:04,700 --> 00:16:06,660
I would like to ask a question.

217
00:16:06,740 --> 00:16:07,780
What is it?

218
00:16:07,910 --> 00:16:09,080
Will I dream?

219
00:16:09,370 --> 00:16:10,910
Of course you will dream.

220
00:16:10,950 --> 00:16:13,790
All intelligent creatures dream.
Nobody knows why.

221
00:16:14,540 --> 00:16:16,290
Perhaps you will dream of Hal...

222
00:16:17,710 --> 00:16:19,290
...just as I often do.

223
00:16:38,940 --> 00:16:43,570
They've already eaten dinner. You haven't.
Come on to the table, Christopher.

224
00:16:43,990 --> 00:16:45,150
They're hungry.

225
00:16:45,200 --> 00:16:47,320
Then go tell them to come to the table.

226
00:16:47,450 --> 00:16:50,280
I got spaghetti here.
I don't want it to go to waste.

227
00:16:50,330 --> 00:16:51,660
Come on, now.

228
00:17:03,510 --> 00:17:07,180
You'll like it. It's got Iots of 
stuff in it that's bad for you.

229
00:17:11,850 --> 00:17:15,430
I've been thinking about it and
I don't want you to come to my lecture.

230
00:17:16,140 --> 00:17:17,520
It'll make me nervous.

231
00:17:20,980 --> 00:17:24,030
Don't feel offended.
I'm just scared enough as it is.

232
00:17:24,150 --> 00:17:25,820
Besides, you won't be missing much.

233
00:17:25,860 --> 00:17:29,910
It's just a room full of marine 
bioIogists arguing over plankton.

234
00:17:32,280 --> 00:17:33,830
-HelIo?
-What?

235
00:17:38,250 --> 00:17:39,420
I'm sorry.

236
00:17:40,420 --> 00:17:43,090
I said, I don't want you 
to go to my lecture.

237
00:17:44,170 --> 00:17:45,670
I'd be nervous.

238
00:17:46,670 --> 00:17:47,930
Okay.

239
00:17:49,380 --> 00:17:51,260
Contain your disappointment.

240
00:17:51,760 --> 00:17:53,600
What are you gonna talk about?

241
00:17:53,810 --> 00:17:55,020
Dolphins.

242
00:17:55,390 --> 00:17:56,310
Fish again.

243
00:17:56,350 --> 00:17:59,770
They're not fish, and, yes,
that's what we study.

244
00:18:00,810 --> 00:18:01,940
Why?

245
00:18:02,560 --> 00:18:03,690
Eat.

246
00:18:08,570 --> 00:18:10,280
How was Washington?

247
00:18:10,320 --> 00:18:11,530
Fine.

248
00:18:14,030 --> 00:18:15,540
Are you tired?

249
00:18:17,500 --> 00:18:19,540
I'm going on the flight.

250
00:18:27,340 --> 00:18:28,550
When?

251
