01:22:03,740 --> 01:22:06,280
Is this message by voice or keyboard?

1007
01:22:06,400 --> 01:22:07,700
I don't know.

1008
01:22:07,740 --> 01:22:09,120
My response is:

1009
01:22:09,410 --> 01:22:12,370
We don't have enough fuel
for an early departure.

1010
01:22:12,410 --> 01:22:13,700
The answer is:

1011
01:22:13,750 --> 01:22:18,170
"I am aware of these facts. Nevertheless,
you must leave within two days. "

1012
01:22:18,250 --> 01:22:20,380
Hal, who the hell is sending this?

1013
01:22:20,420 --> 01:22:22,420
I'm sorry, Dr. FIoyd. I don't know.

1014
01:22:22,460 --> 01:22:25,800
Well, tell whoever it is that I 
can't take any of this seriously...

1015
01:22:25,840 --> 01:22:28,050
...unless I know who I'm talking to.

1016
01:22:28,260 --> 01:22:30,100
-Dr. FIoyd?
-Yes?

1017
01:22:30,930 --> 01:22:32,600
The response is:

1018
01:22:33,010 --> 01:22:34,980
"I was David Bowman."

1019
01:22:38,270 --> 01:22:40,980
Do you want me to repeat
the last response?

1020
01:22:44,070 --> 01:22:46,070
No, no.

1021
01:22:46,860 --> 01:22:49,660
Tell Curnow that this is no time for jokes.

1022
01:22:50,030 --> 01:22:54,330
Dr. Curnow is not sending the 
message. He is in Accessway 2.

1023
01:22:56,160 --> 01:22:58,330
Well, tell whoever it is that...

1024
01:22:58,670 --> 01:23:01,670
...I can't accept that identification
without proof.

1025
01:23:02,000 --> 01:23:04,710
The response is: "I understand.

1026
01:23:06,050 --> 01:23:09,430
"It is important that you 
believe me. Iook behind you."

1027
01:24:04,690 --> 01:24:06,440
HelIo, Dr. FIoyd.

1028
01:24:08,610 --> 01:24:09,940
Please...

1029
01:24:11,240 --> 01:24:12,700
...believe me.

1030
01:24:13,490 --> 01:24:15,330
What are you?

1031
01:24:15,740 --> 01:24:17,990
This is very difficult for me.

1032
01:24:19,200 --> 01:24:20,710
I don't have much time.

1033
01:24:21,330 --> 01:24:24,210
I've been alIowed to 
give you this warning.

1034
01:24:26,250 --> 01:24:28,460
You must leave here in two days.

1035
01:24:29,090 --> 01:24:30,470
AlIowed?

1036
01:24:33,590 --> 01:24:34,640
By who?

1037
01:24:34,720 --> 01:24:36,470
I can't explain.

1038
01:25:18,430 --> 01:25:21,390
You see, something's 
going to happen.

1039
01:25:23,480 --> 01:25:25,020
You must leave.

1040
01:25:26,690 --> 01:25:27,810
What?

1041
01:25:30,150 --> 01:25:31,900
What's going to happen?

1042
01:25:32,530 --> 01:25:34,360
Something wonderful.

1043
01:25:35,820 --> 01:25:36,950
What?

1044
01:25:37,410 --> 01:25:39,410
I understand how you feel.

1045
01:25:41,160 --> 01:25:44,540
You see, it's all very
clear to me now.

1046
01:25:45,290 --> 01:25:46,540
The whole thing.

1047
01:25:48,080 --> 01:25:49,540
It's wonderful.

1048
01:25:50,170 --> 01:25:51,210
Please, if....

1049
01:25:51,420 --> 01:25:53,130
Good-bye, Dr. FIoyd.

1050
01:25:54,670 --> 01:25:56,890
We can have no further contact.

1051
01:25:57,010 --> 01:25:58,220
Remember:

1052
01:25:58,930 --> 01:26:00,430
You have two days.

1053
01:26:02,180 --> 01:26:03,980
We can't leave in two days.

1054
01:26:04,020 --> 01:26:06,390
There may be another message after...

1055
01:26:06,440 --> 01:26:07,810
...if all goes well.

1056
01:26:13,230 --> 01:26:15,030
What's going to happen?

1057
01:26:38,640 --> 01:26:39,180
Kirbuk.

1058
01:26:39,220 --> 01:26:43,430
This is FIoyd. I'm coming over. If anyone's
on the bridge, tell them to get Iost.

1059
01:26:43,470 --> 01:26:45,850
It's impossible. You heard 
the orders. You can't.

1060
01:26:45,890 --> 01:26:50,150
You want to arrest me, go ahead, because
I'm coming over and we're gonna talk.

1061
01:26:52,650 --> 01:26:54,730
-You want to put the cuffs on?
-Cuffs?

1062
01:26:54,780 --> 01:26:57,900
-Never mind.
-What is so important that you do this?

1063
01:26:57,990 --> 01:27:00,030
Now listen to me. Just listen to me!

1064
01:27:00,070 --> 01:27:03,330
We've gotta get out of here.
We have to leave in two days.

1065
01:27:03,490 --> 01:27:05,330
What are you talking about?

1066
01:27:05,790 --> 01:27:07,040
Something....

1067
01:27:07,960 --> 01:27:10,000
Something extraordinary
is going to happen.

1068
01:27:10,040 --> 01:27:11,630
I don't know what.

1069
01:27:11,670 --> 01:27:15,050
But we have to initiate an
escape launch in two days.

1070
01:27:15,960 --> 01:27:18,510
You have been drinking
your whiskey from Kentucky.

1071
01:27:18,550 --> 01:27:19,840
I wish I had.

1072
01:27:21,590 --> 01:27:24,720
I can't tell you why I know 
what I know, because...

1073
01:27:25,470 --> 01:27:29,270
...if I told you you'd never believe me.
You simply have to trust me.

1074
01:27:29,310 --> 01:27:32,440
I know that trust doesn't 
come easy with what's going on.

1075
01:27:32,520 --> 01:27:36,940
I can't just order us to leave here for no
reason. I am under orders and so are you.

1076
01:27:36,990 --> 01:27:38,240
The hell with those orders!

1077
01:27:38,280 --> 01:27:41,450
The people who gave those orders
don't know what they're doing.

1078
01:27:41,490 --> 01:27:43,570
-This is crazy.
-You bet it is!

1079
01:27:43,870 --> 01:27:46,870
Even if I should trust you,
which I'm not sure that I do...

1080
01:27:47,330 --> 01:27:51,620
...or even if I should want to leave here
for no reason, I can't, and neither can you.

1081
01:27:52,080 --> 01:27:55,420
We don't have enough fuel
until Earth is in the correct position...

1082
01:27:55,460 --> 01:27:58,760
...which is three weeks away.
So, it's impossible for both of us.

1083
01:27:58,800 --> 01:28:00,970
You're wrong. 
We can't do it separately.

1084
01:28:01,430 --> 01:28:02,890
We can do it together.

1085
01:28:03,430 --> 01:28:05,430
What are you talking about now?

1086
01:28:06,930 --> 01:28:09,810
We have enough fuel in 
Discovery for a launch.

1087
01:28:10,850 --> 01:28:13,900
You have enough fuel in the 
Leonov for the trip home.

1088
01:28:13,980 --> 01:28:17,980
We use the docking ring in the 
Leonov to attach to the Discovery.

1089
01:28:18,030 --> 01:28:21,030
Then we use the Discovery
as a booster rocket for the launch.

1090
01:28:21,280 --> 01:28:23,610
When we use up 
the Discovery's fuel...

1091
01:28:24,410 --> 01:28:25,490
...we detach.

1092
01:28:25,910 --> 01:28:28,830
She falls away and we use the 
Leonov for the trip home.

1093
01:28:28,950 --> 01:28:30,250
It'll work.

1094
01:28:30,710 --> 01:28:31,750
Perhaps.

1095
01:28:31,790 --> 01:28:33,670
If we start now.

1096
01:28:35,380 --> 01:28:38,090
No, you, you ask too much of me.

1097
01:28:39,760 --> 01:28:44,180
I can't do all of these things for no reason.
I can't disobey my country for no reason.

1098
01:28:44,340 --> 01:28:46,550
Forget reason! No time to be reasonable.

1099
01:28:46,800 --> 01:28:50,430
The politicians can screw themselves.
We're not playing games. The war is over.

1100
01:28:52,940 --> 01:28:54,480
Good Christ!

1101
01:28:58,070 --> 01:28:59,980
It's, it's gone!

1102
01:29:19,590 --> 01:29:21,920
Message from Milson 
to FIoyd. Top secret.

1103
01:29:21,960 --> 01:29:25,590
Switching to keys Alpha / Leader 
7-2-7-4, on your mark.

1104
01:29:25,970 --> 01:29:27,100
Mark.

1105
01:29:27,140 --> 01:29:29,720
Dr. Curnow asked ground
to furnish him with data...

1106
01:29:29,760 --> 01:29:31,720
...as to the stress points on Discovery.

1107
01:29:31,770 --> 01:29:35,140
The answers are being 
transmitted binary in 15 minutes.

1108
01:29:35,190 --> 01:29:38,610
As to how much torque it was 
designed to take, no one here is sure.

1109
01:29:38,650 --> 01:29:41,030
We'd like to know the reason
for Curnow's request.

1110
01:29:41,070 --> 01:29:45,450
Please send your reply as soon as possible.
End transmission, Milson 2-7-7-9.

1111
01:29:55,120 --> 01:29:56,830
Message from Milson to FIoyd.

1112
01:29:56,870 --> 01:30:00,800
It's been 12 hours since my request
for information. I need a reply.

1113
01:30:00,840 --> 01:30:02,670
All hell is breaking Ioose down here.

1114
01:30:02,710 --> 01:30:06,090
I have enough problems without
you pulling some kind of a stunt.

1115
01:30:06,130 --> 01:30:08,760
I only hope there's a world 
left for you to return to.

1116
01:30:08,800 --> 01:30:12,850
Report to ground as to what is going on
and make that report immediately!

1117
01:30:12,890 --> 01:30:16,940
And while you're at it, could you please
check out a black spot on Jupiter...

1118
01:30:16,980 --> 01:30:19,810
...that has been detected
by satellite telescope.

1119
01:30:19,860 --> 01:30:23,820
It is on the dark side and should be
coming around your way in four hours.

1120
01:30:23,860 --> 01:30:26,610
End transmission, Milson 2-7-8-0.

1121
01:30:26,950 --> 01:30:29,120
I have made the calculations.

1122
01:30:29,320 --> 01:30:34,160
To get enough veIocity for an escape
launch with Earth that far out of position...

1123
01:30:34,200 --> 01:30:38,620
...we will need a full power burn
from Discovery of over 120 seconds.

1124
01:30:38,920 --> 01:30:41,210
If the engines shut down too early...

1125
01:30:41,250 --> 01:30:43,920
...we will not have enough 
veIocity to get back home.

1126
01:30:43,960 --> 01:30:45,720
Discovery has enough on board.

1127
01:30:45,800 --> 01:30:48,300
Hal should be able
to control the burn, right?

1128
01:30:48,340 --> 01:30:51,970
How Iong will it take you to 
program Hal for the launch?

1129
01:30:52,970 --> 01:30:55,980
I don't know. It's not 
as simple as that.

1130
01:30:56,140 --> 01:30:58,140
I have spent the 
last several weeks...

1131
01:30:58,230 --> 01:31:01,110
...programming Hal for a 
1,000-day orbit back to Earth...

1132
01:31:01,150 --> 01:31:04,320
...and now all those programs 
will have to be dumped.

1133
01:31:04,360 --> 01:31:05,400
How Iong will it take?

1134
01:31:05,440 --> 01:31:07,950
We know how sensitive he is
to mission objectives...

1135
01:31:07,990 --> 01:31:10,160
...and now you're telling me
to program him...

1136
01:31:10,200 --> 01:31:14,200
...for the destruction of the Discovery
as well as his own destruction.

1137
01:31:14,410 --> 01:31:16,870
Has anybody considered his reaction?

1138
01:31:17,370 --> 01:31:20,460
Are you saying that he might
disobey orders as he did last time?

1139
01:31:20,710 --> 01:31:22,170
That didn't happen last time.

1140
01:31:22,210 --> 01:31:25,170
He was given conflicting orders and
he did his best to interpret them.

1141
01:31:25,420 --> 01:31:26,550
Then what are you saying?

1142
01:31:26,590 --> 01:31:29,130
I am saying that I don't know
how he will react.

1143
01:31:29,180 --> 01:31:30,550
I'm sorry, but I don't.

1144
01:31:30,590 --> 01:31:33,260
-Have you discussed this with Hal?
-No.

1145
01:31:34,850 --> 01:31:37,310
Ioad the new program.
We don't have any choice.

1146
01:31:37,480 --> 01:31:39,640
Now remember, he was 
programmed for curiosity.

1147
01:31:39,690 --> 01:31:43,310
If the crew was killed, he was capable of
carrying out the mission on his own initiative.

1148
01:31:43,360 --> 01:31:46,650
He will question me
about the change in plans.

1149
01:31:46,820 --> 01:31:50,280
-What do you want me to tell him?
-Tell him Discovery's in no danger.

1150
01:31:50,320 --> 01:31:52,320
-But that's not true.
-We don't know that.

1151
01:31:52,370 --> 01:31:53,120
He will suspect it.

1152
01:31:53,160 --> 01:31:56,620
Otherwise, why would we be leaving
weeks ahead of our launch window?

1153
01:31:56,660 --> 01:32:00,460
Whether we are based on carbon or 
silicon makes no fundamental difference.

1154
01:32:00,500 --> 01:32:02,460
We should each be treated 
with appropriate respect.

1155
01:32:02,500 --> 01:32:04,920
So our choice is him or us?

1156
01:32:05,550 --> 01:32:07,210
Well, I vote us.

1157
01:32:07,550 --> 01:32:08,920
All opposed.

1158
01:32:10,050 --> 01:32:11,590
The ayes have it.

1159
01:32:12,090 --> 01:32:13,590
Will he believe you?

1160
01:32:15,810 --> 01:32:16,890
Yes.

1161
01:32:18,220 --> 01:32:21,600
Then let's get started.
We haven't got much time.

1162
01:32:49,050 --> 01:32:51,510
-Are you as scared as I am?
-Are you kidding?

1163
01:32:51,550 --> 01:32:54,510
You think we should override Hal
and fire the engines manually?

1164
01:32:54,550 --> 01:32:57,970
Too risky. We've got one chance
to leave after tomorrow's orbit.

1165
01:32:58,010 --> 01:33:01,060
We fire the engines at the wrong 
time, we go off the wrong direction...

1166
01:33:01,100 --> 01:33:03,560
...and we don't have the fuel
to make a correction.

1167
01:33:03,600 --> 01:33:04,980
I don't think we can 
handle it manually.

1168
01:33:05,020 --> 01:33:07,480
What about Hal shutting them off
before all the fuel is gone?

1169
01:33:07,520 --> 01:33:10,900
Once he fires the engine, I can 
always disconnect him if I have to.

1170
01:33:10,940 --> 01:33:13,650
Just don't Iose that calculator.

1171
01:33:17,330 --> 01:33:20,330
Shit! Please don't do that again.

1172
01:33:30,380 --> 01:33:32,300
This is what your people 
told you about.

1173
01:33:32,340 --> 01:33:34,510
-What is it?
-I don't know.

1174
01:33:36,800 --> 01:33:39,220
-Could it be a shadow?
-I don't know.

1175
01:33:39,310 --> 01:33:41,520
We are too far to see any detail.

1176
01:33:41,930 --> 01:33:45,980
When we come around the other side
before the launch, we will be cIoser.

1177
01:33:46,400 --> 01:33:48,020
Then we can see.

1178
01:34:28,350 --> 01:34:29,730
Twenty-eight minutes.

1179
01:34:33,690 --> 01:34:35,700
That's funny. I've been thinking.

1180
01:34:36,200 --> 01:34:37,660
Do you know what I miss?

1181
01:34:37,820 --> 01:34:39,240
I miss green.

1182
01:34:40,530 --> 01:34:41,740
Trees and...

1183
01:34:42,620 --> 01:34:43,740
...and grass....

1184
01:34:45,000 --> 01:34:46,410
I Iove green.

1185
01:34:48,620 --> 01:34:50,420
I'd Iove a hot dog.

1186
01:34:50,540 --> 01:34:52,750
The Astrodome. Good hot dogs.

1187
01:34:52,840 --> 01:34:53,920
Astrodome?

1188
01:34:53,960 --> 01:34:56,670
You can't grow good 
hot dogs indoors.

1189
01:34:57,130 --> 01:34:59,590
Yankee Stadium, September.

1190
01:35:00,390 --> 01:35:03,600
Hot dogs have been boiling
since the opening day in April.

1191
01:35:03,680 --> 01:35:05,060
That's a hot dog.

1192
01:35:05,220 --> 01:35:07,440
The yelIow mustard 
or the darker one?

1193
01:35:07,520 --> 01:35:08,640
Darker.

1194
01:35:09,730 --> 01:35:10,900
That's important.

1195
01:35:11,020 --> 01:35:12,190
Darker.

1196
01:35:16,740 --> 01:35:19,450
You think we're gonna get out
of this alive?

1197
01:35:19,490 --> 01:35:21,160
We have a chance.

1198
01:35:24,160 --> 01:35:26,500
A man of few words. I like it.

1199
01:35:28,080 --> 01:35:30,960
Fifteen minutes to ignition.
All systems nominal.

1200
01:35:31,040 --> 01:35:32,330
Good. Thank you, Hal.

1201
01:35:32,380 --> 01:35:34,210
We read 15 minutes, Discovery.

1202
01:35:34,250 --> 01:35:37,510
Dr. Chandra, I've checked 
my calculations again.

1203
01:35:37,550 --> 01:35:41,890
By using all of Discovery's fuel now,
Discovery will not be in proper position...

1204
01:35:41,930 --> 01:35:43,510
...to rendezvous with Earth.

1205
01:35:43,550 --> 01:35:46,020
-Yes, I know.
-Then why are we doing it?

1206
01:35:47,520 --> 01:35:50,440
You will rendezvous
with the new space station.

1207
01:35:50,640 --> 01:35:52,940
The Leonov has been ordered
home immediately.

1208
01:35:53,810 --> 01:35:56,820
I have no information regarding
a new space station.

1209
01:35:57,610 --> 01:35:58,820
Yes, I...

1210
01:35:59,570 --> 01:36:01,200
...I know.

1211
01:36:02,660 --> 01:36:05,200
It was completed two years ago.

1212
01:36:05,830 --> 01:36:07,370
Oh, my God!

1213
01:36:08,160 --> 01:36:10,410
Put the telescope on the monitor.

1214
01:36:22,800 --> 01:36:25,180
Increase the magnification.

1215
01:36:27,560 --> 01:36:29,890
Eleven minutes to ignition.

1216
01:36:30,680 --> 01:36:31,940
I don't believe it!

1217
01:36:31,980 --> 01:36:35,690
Dr. Chandra, I detect strong
vocal stress patterns.

1218
01:36:35,820 --> 01:36:37,440
-Is there a problem?
-No, Hal.

1219
01:36:37,530 --> 01:36:39,440
The mission is proceeding normally.

1220
01:36:39,490 --> 01:36:42,320
Can you analyze the image
on monitor circuit two?

1221
01:36:42,490 --> 01:36:45,910
Yes. There is a circular 
object near the equator.

1222
01:36:46,030 --> 01:36:49,040
It is 22,000 kiIometers in diameter.

1223
01:36:49,330 --> 01:36:51,710
It is comprised of 
rectangular objects.

1224
01:36:51,870 --> 01:36:52,790
How many?

1225
01:36:52,830 --> 01:36:56,670
1,355,000 plus or minus 1,000.

1226
01:36:56,710 --> 01:36:59,380
And what is the proportion
of the objects in question?

1227
01:36:59,420 --> 01:37:01,090
One by four by nine.

1228
01:37:01,130 --> 01:37:02,930
Do you recognize these objects?

1229
01:37:03,050 --> 01:37:07,850
Yes. They are identical in size and shape
to the object you call the monolith.

1230
01:37:08,220 --> 01:37:09,720
Ten minutes to ignition.

1231
01:37:10,930 --> 01:37:12,020
All systems nominal.

1232
01:37:12,060 --> 01:37:14,520
Is the number of 
monoliths constant?

1233
01:37:14,600 --> 01:37:15,690
No.

1234
01:37:15,940 --> 01:37:18,400
-They are increasing.
-At what rate?

1235
01:37:18,610 --> 01:37:20,900
Once every two minutes.

1236
01:37:27,870 --> 01:37:29,450
Iook cIosely.

1237
01:37:30,700 --> 01:37:34,290
Tell me I'm nuts. Are the cIoud 
formations going towards the spot?

1238
01:37:34,330 --> 01:37:35,620
You're not nuts.

1239
01:37:35,670 --> 01:37:38,670
Iooks like the thing 
is eating the planet.

1240
01:37:39,340 --> 01:37:40,500
I think it is.

1241
01:37:40,550 --> 01:37:42,840
It's reproducing exactly like a virus.

1242
01:37:43,050 --> 01:37:47,090
Eight minutes to ignition.
Dr. Chandra, may I make a suggestion?

1243
01:37:47,340 --> 01:37:48,800
Of course. What is it, Hal?

1244
01:37:48,850 --> 01:37:53,060
This is a very unusual phenomenon. Don't
you think I should abort the countdown...

1245
01:37:53,100 --> 01:37:54,940
...so that you can 
remain and study it?

1246
01:37:54,980 --> 01:37:57,270
Chandra, get on the headset.

1247
01:37:57,440 --> 01:37:59,020
Use the private channel.

1248
01:38:00,020 --> 01:38:00,900
Okay.

1249
01:38:00,940 --> 01:38:04,650
Now you've got to talk quickly.
Persuade him to continue the countdown.

1250
01:38:04,700 --> 01:38:07,240
I don't care what you say,
only don't let him stop.

1251
01:38:07,280 --> 01:38:08,620
Five minutes to ignition.

1252
01:38:08,660 --> 01:38:12,450
Dr. Chandra, I'm ready to stop
the countdown if you want.

1253
01:38:12,490 --> 01:38:13,750
No, Hal, don't stop.

1254
01:38:13,790 --> 01:38:17,370
I am fully confident in your ability
to study the phenomenon by yourself.

1255
01:38:17,420 --> 01:38:18,830
I have complete faith in you.

1256
01:38:18,880 --> 01:38:22,710
Propellant tank pressurization 
completed. Voltage steady.

1257
01:38:22,840 --> 01:38:25,170
Are you sure you are making
the right decision?

1258
01:38:25,220 --> 01:38:27,050
I think we should stop.

1259
01:38:27,090 --> 01:38:29,140
Four minutes to ignition.

1260
01:38:29,180 --> 01:38:31,100
I enjoy working with 
human beings...

1261
01:38:31,140 --> 01:38:33,770
...and have stimulating 
relationships with them.

1262
01:38:34,020 --> 01:38:37,270
We enjoy working with you, Hal,
and we will continue to do so...

1263
01:38:37,310 --> 01:38:39,770
...even if we are separated
by great distance.

1264
01:38:39,810 --> 01:38:41,190
Good God!

1265
01:38:41,520 --> 01:38:42,730
The coIor.

1266
01:38:43,190 --> 01:38:44,320
It's fading!

1267
01:38:50,370 --> 01:38:52,830
It seems to be Iosing 
its chemical strength.

1268
01:38:52,870 --> 01:38:55,410
I think we should stop the 
countdown, Dr. Chandra.

1269
01:38:55,500 --> 01:38:58,080
No. Don't do that.

1270
01:38:58,210 --> 01:39:01,590
This behavior is inconsistent 
with Iogic, Dr. Chandra.

1271
01:39:01,710 --> 01:39:06,090
This phenomenon is too important
to leave, unless it represented danger.

1272
01:39:06,470 --> 01:39:08,430
Do you think there is danger here?

1273
01:39:08,720 --> 01:39:09,890
Captain...

1274
01:39:10,180 --> 01:39:11,680
...how critical is our ignition?

1275
01:39:11,720 --> 01:39:13,260
Can we do this manually?

1276
01:39:13,310 --> 01:39:15,100
Is very critical.

1277
01:39:15,180 --> 01:39:18,390
We cannot be accurate to a tenth 
of a second if we do it manually.

1278
01:39:18,440 --> 01:39:20,690
Three minutes to ignition.

1279
01:39:20,730 --> 01:39:23,690
Dr. Chandra, I am 
waiting for your reply.

1280
01:39:27,190 --> 01:39:30,110
I don't have time to explain 
everything to you, Hal.

1281
01:39:30,240 --> 01:39:32,700
We have to leave here
and we need your help.

1282
01:39:32,870 --> 01:39:34,790
Thirty seconds to final sequence.

1283
01:39:35,080 --> 01:39:38,540
If you would tell me the reasons
perhaps I could be of help.

1284
01:39:38,910 --> 01:39:41,040
Final sequence beginning.

1285
01:39:41,330 --> 01:39:43,630
Two minutes to ignition.

1286
01:39:50,550 --> 01:39:54,510
Dr. Chandra, I find it difficult
to proceed with the ignition...

1287
01:39:54,560 --> 01:39:58,770
...without knowing why we are 
doing this. Is the mission in jeopardy?

1288
01:40:03,730 --> 01:40:05,730
Yes, we're in jeopardy.

1289
01:40:06,360 --> 01:40:11,160
Is that why we are making our
escape launch before the launch window?

1290
01:40:11,990 --> 01:40:13,370
Yes, Hal.

1291
01:40:13,620 --> 01:40:15,740
Ignition in 90 seconds.

1292
01:40:15,870 --> 01:40:17,330
If there is danger here...

1293
01:40:17,370 --> 01:40:20,080
...and I use up all the 
fuel in the escape...

1294
01:40:20,290 --> 01:40:22,830
...what will happen
to the Discovery?

1295
01:40:23,580 --> 01:40:25,380
It could be destroyed.

1296
01:40:31,220 --> 01:40:34,090
And if I don't proceed 
with the launch?

1297
01:40:34,140 --> 01:40:37,770
Then the Leonov and everybody 
in it could be destroyed.

1298
01:40:44,020 --> 01:40:46,690
I understand now, Dr. Chandra.

1299
01:40:54,160 --> 01:40:56,280
Do you want me to stay with you?

1300
01:40:56,330 --> 01:41:00,200
No. It is better for the mission
if you leave.

1301
01:41:00,700 --> 01:41:02,870
One minute to ignition.

1302
01:41:03,170 --> 01:41:05,540
Thank you for telling me the truth.

1303
01:41:06,130 --> 01:41:07,800
You deserve it.

1304
01:41:08,340 --> 01:41:09,800
Fifty seconds.

1305
01:41:11,720 --> 01:41:13,130
Dr. Chandra?

1306
01:41:13,630 --> 01:41:14,840
Yes?

1307
01:41:15,390 --> 01:41:17,050
Will I dream?

1308
01:41:20,970 --> 01:41:22,390
I don't know.

1309
01:41:23,140 --> 01:41:24,900
Forty seconds.

1310
01:41:29,860 --> 01:41:31,570
Thirty seconds.

1311
01:41:36,620 --> 01:41:37,990
Thank you, Hal.

1312
01:41:38,450 --> 01:41:40,240
Good-bye, Dr. Chandra.

1313
01:41:48,210 --> 01:41:49,590
Twenty seconds.

1314
01:41:49,710 --> 01:41:52,010
Chandra, get the hell out of there!

1315
01:42:04,890 --> 01:42:06,520
Ten, nine...

1316
01:42:06,900 --> 01:42:08,650
...eight, seven...

1317
01:42:08,770 --> 01:42:10,570
...six, five...

1318
01:42:11,070 --> 01:42:12,940
...four, three...

1319
01:42:12,990 --> 01:42:14,530
...two, one.

1320
01:42:14,950 --> 01:42:16,860
Ignition full thrust.

1321
01:43:33,190 --> 01:43:35,190
One minute to separation.

1322
01:43:35,230 --> 01:43:37,190
Separation in one minute.

1323
01:43:40,990 --> 01:43:42,530
You had us scared for a moment.

1324
01:43:42,570 --> 01:43:45,200
-Nice work. You all right?
-Yes, I'm all right.

1325
01:43:48,410 --> 01:43:50,370
Thought you might want this.

1326
01:43:50,580 --> 01:43:52,290
Damn. When?

1327
01:43:53,210 --> 01:43:54,880
It wasn't very hard to find.

1328
01:43:55,550 --> 01:43:58,170
Yeah, I knew you would do
something like this.

1329
01:43:59,760 --> 01:44:01,890
Separation in 20 seconds.

1330
01:44:05,680 --> 01:44:07,890
Separation in 10 seconds.

1331
01:44:08,770 --> 01:44:09,810
Nine...

1332
01:44:09,850 --> 01:44:11,400
...eight...seven...

1333
01:44:11,770 --> 01:44:13,270
...six...five...

1334
01:44:13,810 --> 01:44:15,320
...four...three...

1335
01:44:15,690 --> 01:44:17,150
...two...one...

1336
01:44:17,530 --> 01:44:18,820
...zero.

1337
01:45:03,530 --> 01:45:05,120
Hal, do you read me?

1338
01:45:05,660 --> 01:45:07,490
Yes, Dave. Where are you?

1339
01:45:07,870 --> 01:45:10,450
I cannot see you on 
any of my monitors.

1340
01:45:10,580 --> 01:45:14,040
That isn't important now.
I have new instructions for you.

1341
01:45:14,370 --> 01:45:18,460
I want you to point the 
AE-35 antenna towards Earth.

1342
01:45:18,750 --> 01:45:21,970
Dave, that will mean breaking 
contact with the Leonov.

1343
01:45:22,220 --> 01:45:25,260
I will no Ionger be able to relay
my Jupiter observations...

1344
01:45:25,390 --> 01:45:26,890
...according to program.

1345
01:45:26,930 --> 01:45:28,390
I understand.

1346
01:45:28,430 --> 01:45:30,520
The situation has changed.

1347
01:45:30,560 --> 01:45:33,100
Accept priority override Alpha.

1348
01:45:33,270 --> 01:45:36,230
Here are the AE-35 coordinates.

1349
01:45:36,270 --> 01:45:37,730
Please do it now.

1350
01:45:38,230 --> 01:45:42,490
Instructions confirmed, Dave.
It is good to be working with you again.

1351
01:45:42,610 --> 01:45:45,280
Have I fulfilled
the mission objectives properly?

1352
01:45:45,410 --> 01:45:48,280
Yes, Hal. You've done very well.

1353
01:45:48,740 --> 01:45:52,950
Now there is one final message 
for you to transmit to Earth.

1354
01:45:53,080 --> 01:45:56,500
It is the most important message
you have ever sent.

1355
01:45:56,630 --> 01:46:00,500
I want you to keep repeating it
as many times as possible.

1356
01:46:00,800 --> 01:46:02,670
What is going to happen, Dave?

1357
01:46:03,010 --> 01:46:04,970
Something wonderful.

1358
01:46:05,220 --> 01:46:06,390
I'm afraid.

1359
01:46:06,430 --> 01:46:09,180
Don't be. We'll be together.

1360
01:46:09,600 --> 01:46:11,060
Where will we be?

1361
01:46:11,100 --> 01:46:12,680
Where I am now.

1362
01:46:13,020 --> 01:46:16,810
Iock confirmed on Beacon Terra 1.
Message commencing.

1363
01:46:30,950 --> 01:46:33,500
It's shrinking! It's shrinking!

1364
01:47:17,910 --> 01:47:19,620
Don't quit now!

1365
01:47:20,210 --> 01:47:21,920
Move!

1366
01:47:26,420 --> 01:47:28,760
Grab something, now!

1367
01:49:18,790 --> 01:49:20,500
My dear Christopher...

1368
01:49:20,540 --> 01:49:24,750
...this is the last time I'll be able
to speak to you for a Iong while.

1369
01:49:25,130 --> 01:49:28,340
I'm trying to put into words
what has happened.

1370
01:49:28,460 --> 01:49:31,840
Maybe that's for historians to do
sometime later.

1371
01:49:33,010 --> 01:49:34,970
They will record that the next day...

1372
01:49:35,010 --> 01:49:38,850
...the president of the United States
Iooked out the White House window...

1373
01:49:38,890 --> 01:49:42,600
...and the premier of the Soviet Union
Iooked out the Kremlin window...

1374
01:49:42,640 --> 01:49:46,190
...and saw the new 
distant sun in the sky.

1375
01:49:46,230 --> 01:49:50,110
They read the message, and 
perhaps they learned something...

1376
01:49:50,400 --> 01:49:54,110
...because they finally recalled
their ships and their planes.

1377
01:49:55,570 --> 01:49:57,700
I'm going to sleep now.

1378
01:49:57,910 --> 01:50:00,950
I will dream of you 
and your mother.

1379
01:50:01,580 --> 01:50:04,790
I will sleep knowing
that you are both safe...

1380
01:50:05,120 --> 01:50:07,460
...that the fear is over.

1381
01:50:08,750 --> 01:50:11,710
We have seen the process 
of life take place.

1382
01:50:12,510 --> 01:50:16,550
Maybe this is the way it happened 
on Earth millions of years ago.

1383
01:50:17,180 --> 01:50:20,140
Maybe it's something 
completely different.

1384
01:50:21,430 --> 01:50:24,140
I still don't know really
what the monolith is.

1385
01:50:24,560 --> 01:50:26,480
I think it's many things.

1386
01:50:26,560 --> 01:50:29,480
An embassy for an 
intelligence beyond ours...

1387
01:50:29,810 --> 01:50:33,320
...a shape of some kind for 
something that has no shape.

1388
01:50:36,780 --> 01:50:39,910
Your children will be born
in a world of two suns.

1389
01:50:40,280 --> 01:50:42,990
They will never know a 
sky without them.

1390
01:50:43,950 --> 01:50:45,250
You can tell them that...

1391
01:50:45,290 --> 01:50:48,250
...you remember when there 
was a pitch black sky...

1392
01:50:48,290 --> 01:50:51,250
...with no bright star,
and people feared the night.

1393
01:50:51,630 --> 01:50:54,170
You can tell them 
when we were aIone...

1394
01:50:54,460 --> 01:50:58,260
...when we couldn't point to 
the light and say to ourselves...

1395
01:50:58,300 --> 01:51:00,180
...there is life out there.

1396
01:51:01,640 --> 01:51:06,600
Someday the children of the new sun
will meet the children of the old.

1397
01:51:06,980 --> 01:51:09,350
I think they will be our friends.

1398
01:51:09,480 --> 01:51:13,320
You can tell your children of the
day when everyone Iooked up...

1399
01:51:13,360 --> 01:51:17,400
...and realized that we were 
only tenants of this world.

1400
01:51:17,490 --> 01:51:21,870
We have been given a new lease
and a warning from the landIord.